  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The optimal surgical treatment for insertional Achilles tendinopathy remains unclear. The
      purpose of this study is to evaluate the long-term outcome of surgical treatment by comparing
      the patient reported outcomes of Insertional Achilles Tendinopathy; Achilles tendon
      debridement, excision calcaneal exostosis, Strayer procedure, secondary repair of Achilles
      with flexor hallucis longus (FHL) transfer and Achilles tendon debridement, excision
      calcaneal exostosis, Strayer procedure, secondary repair of Achilles without FHL transfer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
